\u003Cspan>  \u003Cspan>Text after Sudano 2015\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The text can be interpreted as an Italic bimember onomastic formula (see e.g. \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020602\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020602\u003C/a> and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020603\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020603\u003C/a>). For the apheretic use of -εμι at the end of the onomastic formula see \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/EIAZ7ZEW\" target=\"_blank\">Agostiniani 1988-1989\u003C/a>, 195-199; \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/RHXSKW4A\" target=\"_blank\">Agostiniani, Cordano 2002\u003C/a>, 87-89; Sudano 2015, 702-703; commentary of \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020739\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020739\u003C/a>-\u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020745\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020745\u003C/a>, and \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic020766\" target=\"_blank\">ISic020766\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Agostiniani, Cordano 2002 85-87 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002381\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002381\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 2003 150-151 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001843\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001843\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Sudano 2015 702, no. 4, fig. 10 \u003Ca href=\"https://bibli